==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sapotaceous
<hw>Sap`o*ta"ceous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>Of or pertaining to a natural order (<ord>Sapotaceae</ord>) of
(mostly tropical) trees and shrubs, including the star apple, the
Lucuma, or natural marmalade tree, the gutta-percha tree
(<gen>Isonandra</gen>), and the India mahwa, as well as the sapodilla,
or sapota, after which the order is named.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sappan wood</ent>⟦br⟧
